Worked homicide.
I got an eye for detail.

47:04.543 --> 47:07.460
(SCOFFS) Jack tells me
what you're doing

47:07.543 --> 47:08.960
is worth a look.

47:09.043 --> 47:11.377
You want 45th to take
a turn for the worse.

47:12.001 --> 47:13.460
If possible.

47:13.543 --> 47:15.377
JENNIFER PRESTON: And flipping
paper's not gonna get it.

47:17.669 --> 47:20.460
If my team plays, you're gonna
get the best.

47:20.543 --> 47:21.752
No doubt.

47:24.001 --> 47:25.251
(CLEARS THROAT)

47:26.043 --> 47:28.335
Mm! (CHUCKLES)

47:28.418 --> 47:32.794
B.T. Express.
That's a bad jam right there.

47:32.877 --> 47:36.502
(GIGGLES) "Bad jam"?

47:36.585 --> 47:38.085
My father used to say that.

47:38.168 --> 47:41.085
-(CHUCKLES) I know, I'm old.
-(JENNIFER GIGGLES)

47:41.168 --> 47:43.251
-LEON:
Pick up: biscuit and gravy...
-You're not so old.

47:43.335 --> 47:46.251
...two fried eggs with bacon,
three scrambled eggs with salt.

47:46.335 --> 47:48.669
If it's a day or two,
I can look at the schedule.

47:48.752 --> 47:50.794
It's not going to get better.

47:50.877 --> 47:54.001
-I may have to recast your part.
-I know.

47:54.085 --> 47:55.460
(PHONE RINGS)

47:55.543 --> 47:57.877
(CAR HONKS LOUDLY)

48:01.960 --> 48:03.043
How did it go?

48:03.126 --> 48:04.919
How does dinner and dancing
sound?

48:05.001 --> 48:06.043
Really?

48:06.126 --> 48:07.794
-You feel up for it?
-Definitely.

48:08.710 --> 48:09.794
Okay.

48:12.585 --> 48:14.168
(SIGHS HEAVILY)

48:15.293 --> 48:16.794
-You want that?
-Uh-huh.

48:25.418 --> 48:28.418
(WOMAN SINGING "THE WILD ROVER,"
MUFFLED)

48:28.502 --> 48:32.043
♪ And it's no, nay, never ♪

48:32.126 --> 48:35.293
♪ No, nay, never, no more ♪

48:35.377 --> 48:37.710
♪ Will I play... ♪

48:37.794 --> 48:39.210
MATTHEW: (OUTSIDE DOOR)
Your mother.

48:39.293 --> 48:41.210
She took the worst of it.

48:41.293 --> 48:43.251
Jesus, I nearly killed
that woman.

48:43.335 --> 48:45.251
No, I did kill her.

48:45.335 --> 48:47.460
I killed her spirit.

48:47.543 --> 48:51.752
And if you hadn't run,
I would have killed yours too.

48:51.835 --> 48:53.043
And I...

48:55.794 --> 48:57.210
REG:
...damn clothes if she wants.

48:57.293 --> 48:59.502
BOYFRIEND: You're a bitch, too.
(LAUGHS)

49:02.752 --> 49:04.585
BOYFRIEND:
Hey, you're so bad!

49:04.669 --> 49:07.001
REG:
Can't be running around doing
laundry for all these divas...

49:07.085 --> 49:09.335
MATTHEW: I think
if I could see your face...

49:09.919 --> 49:11.168
just once.

49:13.418 --> 49:14.877
I think if I could...

49:16.502 --> 49:18.335
see you as you are...

49:20.001 --> 49:21.669
I would have the strength to go.

49:21.752 --> 49:24.585
(FOOTSTEPS CLIMBING STAIRS
IN DISTANCE)

49:34.377 --> 49:35.585
(SIGHS)

49:37.794 --> 49:40.710
(LATCH CLICKS, RATTLING)

49:42.710 --> 49:45.543
(RATTLING, LOCK CLICKS)

49:46.669 --> 49:49.585
(DOOR CREAKS)

50:02.043 --> 50:03.085
(SNIFFS)

50:05.835 --> 50:08.794
(MAN YELLING IN SPANISH)

50:08.877 --> 50:11.377
ABBY:
I wish I could do what you do.

50:11.460 --> 50:14.126
Art belongs out here
where everyone can see it.

50:17.585 --> 50:20.043
I'm meeting some friends
at Paradise Garage.

50:21.960 --> 50:23.085
Can you dance?

50:24.043 --> 50:26.585
-Shit yeah.
-Come with me.

50:40.293 --> 50:43.919
(MAN YELLS IN SPANISH, LAUGHS)

50:46.835 --> 50:49.293
I was 50-50
you'd pull away.

50:50.293 --> 50:51.627
(BOTH CHUCKLE)

50:52.794 --> 50:54.085
(CLEARS THROAT)

50:54.168 --> 50:56.210
(WOMAN YELLING IN SPANISH)

50:56.293 --> 50:59.293
♪ ("#5 GO BANG!" BY DINOSAUR L
FRANCOIS K MIX PLAYS) ♪

51:16.627 --> 51:18.960
♪ Bang, bang, bang,
Go bang go ♪

51:20.418 --> 51:22.210
♪ Bang bang, go bang bang ♪

51:22.293 --> 51:24.335
♪ Bang, bang, bang,
Go bang go ♪

51:35.335 --> 51:36.794
♪ (EASY LISTENING MUSIC PLAYS) ♪

51:36.877 --> 51:38.001
BERNICE: Hey.

51:38.877 --> 51:40.168
Yeah, it's cost per head.

51:41.168 --> 51:42.585
Yep.

51:42.669 --> 51:43.919
This all from last night?

51:44.001 --> 51:45.460
Yup. What did I tell you?

51:45.543 --> 51:47.627
BERNICE: Yeah, you too.
Have a good one.

51:47.710 --> 51:49.293
Maybe we got something here.

51:50.710 --> 51:53.251
Another guy asking if we could
send a few more girls

51:53.335 --> 51:54.418
over to the island.

51:54.502 --> 51:56.335
We need to hire more drivers.

51:56.418 --> 51:58.210
I ain't paying for nobody's gas.

52:01.085 --> 52:05.377
WOMAN: (SINGING) ♪ Don't wanna
Tell you no stories ♪

52:05.460 --> 52:09.418
♪ Don't wanna tell you
No lies ♪

52:09.502 --> 52:13.460
♪ I saw your man
About an hour ago ♪

52:13.543 --> 52:16.752
-♪ With a girl named
Nellie Bly ♪
-What's her name?

52:16.835 --> 52:19.877
Beats me. It's an open mic.
Wanna put your name down?

52:20.335 --> 52:21.960
Me? No.

52:22.043 --> 52:24.001
♪ But he's doing you wrong ♪

52:27.210 --> 52:31.168
♪ Frankie went to
Her hotel room ♪

52:31.251 --> 52:34.210
♪ And drew out her big .44 ♪

52:35.543 --> 52:39.293
♪ Shot her man three times
In the back ♪

52:39.377 --> 52:42.669
♪ Through a great big
Hardwood door ♪

52:42.752 --> 52:44.460
♪ And he was her man ♪

52:44.543 --> 52:47.001
♪ ("ONE STEP UP, TWO STEPS BACK"
BY BETTY WRIGHT PLAYS) ♪

52:47.085 --> 52:51.168
♪ One step up
Two steps back to you ♪

52:53.001 --> 52:56.919
♪ Try to leave but I... ♪

52:57.001 --> 52:59.126
Wow, this is... amazing.

53:01.710 --> 53:03.001
Do we dance?

53:03.085 --> 53:05.710
-First time here?
-I-- I've never been to a club

53:05.794 --> 53:06.835
like this.

53:06.919 --> 53:09.085
This place isn't just a club.

53:16.710 --> 53:19.543
♪ And love's smoldering ashes ♪

53:19.627 --> 53:22.585
♪ Spark a burning fire ♪

53:28.001 --> 53:30.752
-Hey!
-PAUL: Hey!

53:34.085 --> 53:35.293
TOD: Hey!

53:38.835 --> 53:40.585
I'm so glad you made it.

53:40.669 --> 53:42.001
I brought a friend.

53:42.085 --> 53:44.043
-Hi, friend.
-Hello, friend!

53:44.126 --> 53:46.168
-Hi. Pilar.
-Paul.

53:46.251 --> 53:47.502
Hi, Paul.

53:51.001 --> 53:53.585
♪ ("MAKE ME A BELIEVER"
BY LUTHER VANDROSS PLAYS) ♪

53:53.669 --> 53:54.877
Michael.

53:54.960 --> 53:56.752
-How is it going?
-Hey, Mr. Pipilo.

53:56.835 --> 53:59.377
-Haven't seen you in a while.
-Frankie still here?

53:59.460 --> 54:00.460
V.I.P.

54:01.418 --> 54:02.543
And Vincent?

54:02.627 --> 54:04.293
He's in the back.
Want me to get him?

54:05.460 --> 54:09.251
Nah, we're good.
'Night, Michael.

54:09.335 --> 54:10.418
All right.

54:13.877 --> 54:15.752
I heard you had a good night.

54:15.835 --> 54:17.627
(SCOFFS) Look, Rudy.

54:17.710 --> 54:19.293
RUDY PIPILO: "Look, Rudy"?

54:19.377 --> 54:21.168
(INHALES) It's not how it looks.

54:21.251 --> 54:23.168
What's it look like, Frankie?

54:23.251 --> 54:24.460
I'm just saying...

54:24.543 --> 54:26.293
Yeah,
you're always fucking saying.

54:27.585 --> 54:29.126
This is how I blow off steam.

54:29.210 --> 54:31.502
-I got a right to have fun.
-Yeah, do ya?

54:33.126 --> 54:34.543
Come on, have a drink.

54:34.627 --> 54:35.752
No, Frankie.

54:35.835 --> 54:36.835
Sit.

54:39.669 --> 54:43.085
-You brain-dead piece of shit.
-Ooh!

54:43.168 --> 54:45.043
All right. That's enough.

54:45.126 --> 54:47.168
You don't know shit
about enough.

54:47.251 --> 54:49.335
GAMBLER: The fuck you know
about psychology?

54:49.418 --> 54:51.293
Okay, all right, fine.

54:52.835 --> 54:54.502
You know what?

54:54.585 --> 54:57.335
Take your money. It's five Gs.

54:57.418 --> 54:58.585
No.

54:59.752 --> 55:03.710
Come on. I want you to have it.

55:03.794 --> 55:05.835
-No.
-C'mon, Rudy.

55:13.168 --> 55:15.335
Make me say no one more time.

55:34.710 --> 55:35.919
(SIGHS)

55:36.960 --> 55:38.043
(SNIFFLES)

55:39.085 --> 55:42.960
Dad... What do you want from me?

55:43.710 --> 55:44.752
Nothing.

55:46.251 --> 55:49.543
(SCOFFS)
How did you even find me?

55:51.460 --> 55:54.001
-The movies.
-(MELISSA SCOFFS)

55:54.085 --> 55:55.919
One of the guys at work saw
one of the movies

55:56.001 --> 55:57.835
and didn't have sense enough
not to tell me.

55:57.919 --> 55:59.168
Fuck him!

55:59.251 --> 56:00.669
MATTHEW: Oh, I don't care
about the movies.

56:00.752 --> 56:04.210
And I don't care
about any of it. I just--

56:04.293 --> 56:05.960
I just knew that you were alive.

56:06.043 --> 56:09.919
And I wanted to see you.
That's all.

56:13.377 --> 56:16.126
(INHALES)
Well, now you've seen me.

56:19.585 --> 56:20.752
(WEAKLY) Yeah.

56:21.627 --> 56:23.627
(DOG BARKING)

56:25.126 --> 56:26.627
(SIGHS)

56:38.877 --> 56:40.502
REG: Liss, open up, baby.

56:40.585 --> 56:41.794
Come on, now.

56:44.293 --> 56:45.627
(MELISSA SIGHS)

57:21.585 --> 57:24.085
-One more dance.
-No, I'm sitting this one out.

57:24.168 --> 57:25.627
Come on!

57:25.710 --> 57:28.627
-Abby, you guys go. We'll watch.
-Paul, you love this song. Go!

57:28.710 --> 57:30.377
♪ ("ANGEL IN MY POCKET"
BY CHANGE PLAYING) ♪

57:30.460 --> 57:32.085
All right, one dance,
but then home.

57:32.168 --> 57:33.960
(CHUCKLES) Yeah.

57:36.585 --> 57:38.502
♪ There's an angel
In my pocket ♪

57:38.585 --> 57:42.293
♪ I keep movin' on ♪

57:44.335 --> 57:46.543
♪ There's an angel
In my pocket ♪

57:46.627 --> 57:48.543
♪ Keeping me on my toes ♪

57:52.043 --> 57:53.627
♪ There's an angel
In my pocket ♪

57:53.710 --> 57:57.210
♪ There's someone that cares
For me ♪

57:59.502 --> 58:01.669
♪ There's an angel
In my pocket... ♪

58:08.251 --> 58:11.043
♪ (MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

59:22.960 --> 59:24.669
VINCENT MARTINO:
I've been in Times Square
a long time.

59:25.335 --> 59:26.251
Whatever happened,

59:26.502 --> 59:28.502
whatever's already been said
and done, just...

59:28.585 --> 59:29.627
let it be.

59:30.293 --> 59:32.794
♪ (MUSIC PLAYS) ♪

59:34.001 --> 59:36.543
EILEEN MERRELL: What I'm after
is the wildest shit.

59:36.627 --> 59:38.168
It's already in all our heads.

59:39.627 --> 59:42.251
Something's really happenin',
and you're not with us.

59:42.627 --> 59:43.877
Do you even know what you want?

59:44.377 --> 59:47.210
GENE GOLDMAN:
Everything is one step forward,
two steps back.

59:47.293 --> 59:48.335
(GUNSHOTS)

59:49.669 --> 59:50.752
Make a wish.

59:50.835 --> 59:52.168
♪ (MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪
